This place is actually pretty great. The staff is always friendly, helpful, and generous with portions. The food is actually really tasty, which I was somewhat surprised given the lack of name recognition for the chain and some of the past mediocre reviews.  I actually started going to Moe's instead of Chipotle. The burritos are a little more expensive, but they really cram a load of ingredients in there. There are more ingredient options, and you get lots of chips and unlimited salsa included in the cost of the burrito! The salsa options really put this place over the top, especially the (seasonal) Scorpion Pepper salsa. Delicious!

I usually stop by this place on Saturday's after work. Im always well greeted and treated by an elder African American female. However, I visited on Friday, January 12, 2018 and was very displeased with the service & food provided. Some of the food looked old and dry as if it had been sitting there for a very long time. I requested queso and received the last corner that wasn't a whole spoonful, after watching them poor two full spoons onto the person ahead of me plate. When I asked for a full spoon I was told more would be coming out shortly and when it did, I was charged for it. They did NOT charge the person in front of me for extra queso. Yes, I absolutely paid attention to everything. Then, the person ordered a quesadilla that was still cooking on the stove while my order was ready. They made me wait (almost 10 mins) until his food was done and ready to ring up. The worst service ever! I literally almost walked out. I got home and the meat that I did choose and thought looked fresh was dry with sauce placed over it to make it look fresh, and filled with fat/gristle. I am so disappointed!! I will stick to Saturday's. I've never been disappointed neither received this kind of service on a Saturday early afternoon, around noon.
